==Korean==
===Noun===
'''구멍''' (gumeong)

#[[hole]]
#*바지에 '''구멍'''이 났다. (''baji-e gumeong-i nattda''.) <br> [I’ve] got a hole in my trousers. <br> Literally, "A hole appeared in my trousers."
#*벽에 '''구멍'''을 뚫다. (''byeog-e '''gumeong'''eul ttulhda'') <br> To drill a '''hole''' in a wall.

====Related terms====
*[[오존]] 구멍 (''ojon gumeong'') &mdash; ozone hole
*[[검]]은 구멍 (''geom-eun gumeong'') &mdash; [[black hole]]

====Synonyms====
* (obsolete) 구무 (gumu), 굳 (gud, gut), 굼ㄱ (gumg), 굿 (gus) [[hole]], [[hollow]] (cf. [[gut]] or [[alimentary canal]])
* [[구덩이]] (gudeongI) [[pit]], [[hollow]]
* [[굴]] (gul) [[hole]], [[hollow]]; [[den]], [[burrow]]; [[cave]]; [[tunnel]] 


